Value: Mamba Exploration Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as an early-stage exploration and development company in Australia. It primarily explores for gold, copper, nickel, manganese, cobalt, silver, and other deposits. The company holds a 100% interest Darling Range project covers approximately 75km2 located north-east of Perth; a 100% interest Calyerup Creek project comprising approximately 45km2 located in Western Australia; and 100% in Ashburton and Kimberley project located in Western Australia. Mamba Exploration Limited was incorporated in 2020 and is headquartered in Perth, Australia.
